MOD=1000000007 
for t in range(int(input())): 
    print('Case '+str(t+1)+':')
    n,q=map(int,input().split())
    for i in range(q):
        x=input().strip()
        xlen=len(x)
        if xlen>n:
            print(0)
            continue 
        rem=n-xlen
        remtot=pow(26,rem,MOD)
        ans=remtot*(rem+1)%MOD 
        print(ans)

def power(x, y) : 
    res = 1     # Initialize result 
  
    # Update x if it is more 
    # than or equal to p 
    x = x % mod  
  
    while (y > 0) : 
          
        # If y is odd, multiply 
        # x with result 
        if ((y & 1) == 1) : 
            res = (res * x) % mod 
  
        # y must be even now 
        y = y >> 1      # y = y/2 
        x = (x * x) % mod
